Let the points \( A = (1, 2) \), \( B = (4, 6) \), and \( C = (7, 2) \). If vector \( \mathbf{u} \) is defined as \( \overrightarrow{AB} \) and vector \( \mathbf{v} \) is defined as \( \overrightarrow{AC} \), find the angle \( \theta \) between the vectors \( \mathbf{u} \) and \( \mathbf{v} \) in degrees. 

[asy]
pair A, B, C;

A = (1, 2);
B = (4, 6);
C = (7, 2);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
dot("$A$", A, N);
dot("$B$", B, NE);
dot("$C$", C, SE);

label("$\theta$", (B + C)/2 + (0,0.5));
[/asy]
